Considering the diversity of plants involved, their medicinal value,<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Mazid|first1=Mohd.|last2=Khan|first2=Taqi Ahmed|last3=Mohammad|first3=Firoz|title=Medicinal Plants of Rural India: A Review of Use by Indian Folks|journal=Indo Global Journal of Pharmaceutical Sciences|date=2012|volume=2|issue=3|url=http://iglobaljournal.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/9.-Mohd-Mazid-et-al-2012.pdf|accessdate=25 December 2015}}</ref> and association with Nakshatras, many organisations are popularizing the creation of Nakshatravanam.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nakshatra vana— A treasure trove of plants|url=http://www.deccanherald.com/content/269250/nakshatra-vana-treasure-trove-plants.html|publisher=[[Deccan Herald]]|accessdate=24 December 2015|date=2012-08-04}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ofsdp.org/publication/nl_july_sept_2011_adj.pdf|accessdate=24 December 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Nakshatravanam' planned|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/nakshatravanam-planned/article7273428.ece|publisher=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=24 December 2015|newspaper=The Hindu|date=June 2015|last1=Reporter|first1=Staff}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Nakshatravanam dedicated|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Coimbatore/nakshatravanam-dedicated/article6927044.ece|newspaper=The Hindu|accessdate=24 December 2015|date=2015-02-23|last1=Reporter|first1=Staff}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title='Nakshatravanam' At Putharikandam Maidan|url=http://www.yentha.com/news/view/1/Nakshatravanam-at-Putharikandam-Maidan|accessdate=24 December 2015}}</ref>
